This fixture is a small Go module for find-all-references integration
coverage against gopls. A single exported function is declared in one file and
referenced twice from another so cross-file reference resolution is exercised.

Markers embedded in the source drive the test:

  decl=Greeting marks the function declaration queried by textDocument/references.
  use=Greeting  marks the first cross-file call site.
  use2=Greeting marks the second cross-file call site.

-- go.mod --
module referencesfixture

go 1.27

-- greet.go --
package main

func Greeting(name string) string { // decl=Greeting
	return "hello " + name
}

-- main.go --
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
	fmt.Println(Greeting("gopher")) // use=Greeting
	fmt.Println(Greeting("mcp")) // use2=Greeting
}
